docs.abstract: Representative-elect Alexandria Ocasio-Cortez joined activists in a protest in Representative Nancy Pelosi’s office, putting leaders on notice that the new House may be divided.
docs.snippet: Representative-elect Alexandria Ocasio-Cortez joined activists in a protest in Representative Nancy Pelosi’s office, putting leaders on notice that the new House may be divided.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Freshman orientation for new members of Congress had barely begun when Alexandria Ocasio-Cortez, the 29-year-old darling of the progressive left and newly elected congresswoman from New York, visited Nancy Pelosi’s office for the first time. She was not there to meet the House Democratic leader.

headline.main: A Left-Flank Protest on Day 1 Signals a Democratic House Divided
headline.print_headline: Divisions on Day One: Party’s Progressive Star Protests House Leader

byline.original: By Sheryl Gay Stolberg and Emily Cochrane

docs.abstract: The president offered an unabashed endorsement of Senator Cindy Hyde-Smith, who is under fire over comments that seemed to embrace the state’s racist history.

docs.lead_paragraph: TUPELO, Miss. — President Trump returned to the campaign trail in Mississippi on Monday to offer an unabashed endorsement of a Republican candidate under fire for comments that critics said embraced the state’s segregationist history.

docs.abstract: After Mr. Tillerson said that President Trump regularly pressed for action that would violate the law, the president fired back on Twitter.

docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — President Trump denounced his first secretary of state, Rex W. Tillerson, as “dumb as a rock” and “lazy as hell” on Friday after Mr. Tillerson said that the president had regularly pushed him to take actions that were illegal.

docs.abstract: The West Virginia senator’s support for coal has drawn fire from progressives, who say he should not be given a big voice in the party’s climate change policy.
docs.snippet: The West Virginia senator’s support for coal has drawn fire from progressives, who say he should not be given a big voice in the party’s climate change policy.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — During his first run for the Senate in 2010, Joe Manchin III, the Democrat from West Virginia, took aim — literally — at a climate change bill, shooting a bullet through it in a television ad. Now some Democrats are taking aim at Mr. Manchin, declaring him unfit to be the top Democrat on the committee that handles climate change.

headline.main: Joe Manchin Faces Liberal Opposition in Bid to Be Energy Panel’s Top Democrat
headline.print_headline: Effort Builds to Deny West Virginia Democrat a Key Senate Role on Climate

docs.abstract: The top air pollution official in the Trump administration had been a lawyer for polluting industries. They are now benefiting from his new role.
docs.snippet: The top air pollution official in the Trump administration had been a lawyer for polluting industries. They are now benefiting from his new role.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — As a corporate lawyer, William L. Wehrum worked for the better part of a decade to weaken air pollution rules by fighting the Environmental Protection Agency in court on behalf of chemical manufacturers, refineries, oil drillers and coal-burning power plants.

headline.main: As Trump Dismantles Clean Air Rules, an Industry Lawyer Delivers for Ex-Clients
headline.print_headline: Industry Insider Pushes to Erode Clean Air Rules

docs.abstract: For 150 years, the justices have sat, not always happily, for an extraordinary series of group portraits
docs.snippet: For 150 years, the justices have sat, not always happily, for an extraordinary series of group portraits
docs.lead_paragraph: Justice Brett M. Kavanaugh stood in the back row, on the far right, beaming. Justice Ruth Bader Ginsburg, recovering from a fall, sat in front of him, grimacing. Off to her right, Justice Stephen G. Breyer appeared to chuckle at a joke he had just recalled.

headline.main: The Stories Behind the Supreme Court’s Class Photos
headline.print_headline: Herding Unruly Justices for a Family Portrait
